         <t:div type="edition" xml:lang="gez">
            <t:div type="textpart" subtype="colophon" xml:id="coloph1">
               <t:ab>ተተርጐመት፡ ዛቲ፡ <t:sic resp="PRS10171Wright">መጽፍ፡</t:sic> አምዓረቢ፡ ወእስከ፡ ግዕዝ፡ በ፱ዓመተ፡ መንግሥቱ፡ ለንጉሥነ፡ ፋሲለደስ፡ ዘተሰምየ፡ ቈስጥንጢኖስ። ፷፻ወ፱፻ወ፹ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፡ ጥንትዮን፡ ፪አበቅቴ፡ ፯ወበ፲፻ወ፪፻ወ፬እምዓመተ፡ ሰማዕታት፡ ወዘአጽሐፋ፡ ፍሥሓ፡ ጽዮን።
            </t:ab>
               <t:note>The copied colophon of translation (taken from <t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BLorient713">London, British Library, BL Oriental 713</t:ref>) gives the  date of translation, 9th year of the reign of Fāsiladas or Constantine, 6980 Ethiopian Calendar, i.e. <t:date notBefore="1487" notAfter="1488"/>. There is some mistake here as <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS4015Fasilada">Fāsiladas</t:persName>' s reign only started in 1632. The reference is probably
                  to Emperor <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS3874eskender">ʾƎskǝndǝr</t:persName>, or Constantine, who began to reign in <t:date>November 1478</t:date>.</t:note>
               
            </t:div>
         </t:div>
